radiographic_examinations.findings: Dilated, fluid-filled appendix measuring up to 8 mm with adjacent fat stranding. No drainable fluid collection or extraluminal air to suggest perforation. Visualized lung fields are within normal limits. No evidence of pleural or pericardial effusion. Liver, pancreas, spleen, kidneys, gastrointestinal tract, and reproductive organs are unremarkable. No evidence of focal lesions, hydronephrosis, or significant abnormalities.
